    :description
    "vis-foundation: ONE classpath jar, ONE SCI alias `vis/`, three cooperating surfaces \u2014 introspection (turn / conversation / diagnose / failures / var-history / find-attempts / extensions catalog), file I/O (cat / ls / rg / edit / write), and environment awareness (snapshot / git / languages / monorepo / refresh!). Owns the `<environment>` block in the system prompt. Replaces the legacy three-package split (vis-common-foundation + vis-common-editing + vis-common-environment) plus the dropped `fs/` alias."
    :content
    "# vis-foundation

Pkg: `com.blockether/vis-foundation`. Src: `extensions/common/vis-foundation/`.
Canonical: inlined under `[vis :docs \"README.md\"]` in `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn`. LLM reads via `(vis/extension-readme 'vis)`.

ONE alias `vis/` bundles everything the agent needs to read its own state, work the filesystem, and see the host environment. Replaces three legacy packages (`vis-common-foundation`, `vis-common-editing`, `vis-common-environment`) and drops the `fs/` alias entirely \u2014 the editing tools resolve every path internally against `(fs/cwd)` already, so the model never had to do path math directly.

## Sections

### Introspection (read your own state)

Pure reads off the same DB tables the projection layer uses; failures return nil/[] never throw.

```clojure
(vis/turn)                        ; in-flight turn snapshot
(vis/conversation cid?)           ; conversation tree (turns / iterations / cost)
(vis/conversations channel?)      ; list every conversation
(vis/conversation-forks cid?)     ; every conversation_state row (trunk + forks)
(vis/query-retries qid)           ; every query_state row (original + retries)
(vis/var-history 'sym)            ; version timeline for a SCI def
(vis/find-attempts pat cid?)      ; regex search over executed code
(vis/find-attempts-everywhere pat) ; same, across EVERY conversation in the DB (heavy)
(vis/failures cid?)               ; classify failed iterations
(vis/failures-everywhere)         ; same, DB-wide (heavy)
(vis/diagnose cid?)               ; counts + repetition-loop detection + next actions
(vis/extensions)                  ; loaded ext catalog
(vis/extension-docs ext-ref)      ; declared doc summaries (no content)
(vis/extension-doc ext-ref name)  ; full doc descriptor incl. :content
(vis/extension-readme ext-ref)    ; README :content shortcut
```

### File I/O (read + write)

Every return value is a Clojure map; no prose embedded in tool output.

```clojure
(vis/cat path)                    ; -> {:path :offset :total-lines :truncated-by :lines}
(vis/cat path opts)               ; opts {:offset N :limit M :char-limit C}
(vis/ls path)                     ; -> nested {:name :path :type :size :children} tree
(vis/ls path opts)                ; opts {:depth :hidden? :respect-gitignore?}
(vis/rg [\"a\" \"b\"] path)       ; -> {:hits [{:path :line :text} ...] :truncated-by :limit | :end-of-results}
                                  ; patterns = non-empty vec of LITERAL substrings (PCRE metacharacters auto-escaped)
                                  ; for genuine regex: (re-seq #\"...\" (str/join \"\\n\" (:lines (vis/cat path))))
(vis/edit path s r)               ; -> {:path :bytes-before :bytes-after}; replace FIRST `s`->`r`; `s` must be unique
(vis/edit path s r {:line N})     ; disambiguate by line
(vis/write path content)          ; -> {:path :bytes}; overwrite or create
```

For structured Clojure edits use the sibling `vis-language-clojure` extension (alias `clj/`).

### Environment awareness

Bounded host + git + language + monorepo snapshot, computed lazily and cached per cwd.

```clojure
(vis/snapshot)        ; full snapshot {:host :git :languages :monorepo}
(vis/git)             ; git submap or nil
(vis/languages)       ; bounded language scan
(vis/monorepo)        ; monorepo shape detection
(vis/render)          ; same render as the system prompt's `<environment>` block
(vis/refresh!)        ; drop cache, recompute; useful after substantial working-tree changes
```

The `<environment>` block in the system prompt (cwd / user / platform / shell / locale / jvm / git / languages / monorepo) is rendered from the same snapshot. Drop this jar -> drop the block.

## Why one alias?

Pre-merge the agent had to context-switch between four aliases (`foundation/`, `vis/`, `fs/`, `environment/`) to compose a single thought. The aliases were artifacts of separate jars, not separate concerns from the model's POV. Collapsing to `vis/` keeps every primitive one short prefix away \u2014 the model's iteration code reads more like prose, less like a multi-namespace boundary."
